    <pre>Regarding the OpenHatch.org about box, on the landing page:

First of all, thanks for adding that box and doing a good starting job on the
text. I just edited it for a while, and came up with something I'm going to
deploy. I want to make sure that it's something people are happy with, so I'm
going to email Devel to see what people think. I've already deployed it, though.

Some feedback on the patch:

* Please use quotes around HTML attribute values.

For the second patch, it applied great, and it made good sense to me.

(Karen, if you have thoughts on the front page CSS changes to
<a href="http://openhatch.org/">http://openhatch.org/</a> (namely, when you're not logged-in -- the blog and OH
activity are about the same width) by all means say so here and/or file other
bugs. I wanted to CC: you on this update to this ticket, but for now I'm marking
it as resolved.)

It's super great to have these patches. They're deployed!</pre>
